{
  "text": "In the current scenario, path dependency is emphasised by the choice of incumbents to invest in FTTC [CITATION_1] , while wireless technologies are unlikely to play a central role in NGA market due to their limited bandwidth (KPMG, 2010) . Furthermore, the role of public sector has changed significantly over the past decade, with autonomous initiatives of local authorities being replaced by top-down interventions coordinated by central governments (Broadband Commission, 2013) .",
